vehicles.name: TGV Postal Cab (F) (P5)
vehicles.description:
Power car facing forwards, with the pantograph up to 5 blocks height.

The TGV Postal was introduced in 1984 and is instantly recognizable by its bright yellow La Poste livery. Based on modified TGV Sud-Est (PSE) units, the postal variants had their passenger compartments replaced with spacious cargo areas capable of holding up to 100 tons of mail and parcels. Operating primarily on overnight routes between Paris and Lyon , they could reach speeds of 270 km/h, dramatically cutting delivery times. For three decades, these specialized trains silently whisked letters and packages across France until changing postal needs led to their retirement in 2015.
